---

Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #deep pan{} over a medium-high heat and cook @onion{1}(diced), 
@carrots{2}(diced), and @celery sticks{2}(diced), including any leaves, for ~{15%minutes} until 
softened. Stir in @tomato purée{2%tbsp}, @garlic{3%cloves}(chopped), and @rosemary or 
@thyme sprigs{3}. Cook for a few minutes until the purée is caramelised. 

Pour in @vegetable stock{1%litre}, @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}, @chickpeas{1%400g can} 
(and the liquid from the can), and @?parmesan rind{} (optional), if you have one. Simmer 
for ~{15%minutes}.

Pour boiling water over @orzo{150g} in a heatproof bowl and set aside for ~{15%minutes}. 
Drain the orzo, add to the pan, and cook for ~{5-8%minutes} until the orzo is tender. Fish out 
and discard the rosemary stalks and cheese rind, then season well. Drizzle over 
@extra virgin olive oil{} to serve.